{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1478591503,"nonce":"y2cUP7eAl0TlNIRPPr6u+ZBeAhY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI1OTA2ODk0MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1025#issuecomment-259068941"},"message":"I wanted to test this but the bioconda build of samtools 1.2 did not let me do this because linking with ncurses on Arch is broken. The current build of 1.2 was built on the old build system and is incorrectly linked to the system build of ncurses. This problem shall appear more often  in the future as distros shall update their ncurses.\n\nThe 1.2 directory is not present as bioconda-recipe anymore. I will try to recover this for the sake of reproducibility.","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1478792162,"nonce":"j1qtZNir/bayyD6ZI7E2yxYHoUw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDg1NDY0NTExNA=="},"added":["bug"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1478792937,"nonce":"kfOZuX95yIU6b7MpUlhU6pcgbYs=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI1OTcyNTE4Nw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1025#issuecomment-259725187"},"message":"There is indeed weird behaviour in arg-parsing of samtools 1.2. It feels like it starts parsing from arg[2] instead of arg[1]. You could get it back working again by running `samtools sort -f unsorted.bam sorted.bam`. Anyway, I believe this affects _./tools/bedtools/bamToBed.xml_ when the `-bedpe` option is selected. In hisat it seems to work properly. Trinity I can't confirm because it's an internal tool dependency, but it has passed the travis test. BWAMETH may be affected. BCFtools does not use `sort` but `mpileup`. JBrowse may be affected but I can't confirm this either because it's an internal tool dependency.","files":null}]}